RoundShield_8001.name: Dryadâ€™s Wrath
RoundShield_8001.description: Crafted using spirit wood by a powerful ancient Druid who received permission from the forest Dryads to imbue it with the power of nature.
RoundShield_8001.effect: Gain 1 impact resistance. Blocking a melee attack deals 0.03% of the damage blocked to the opponent.

Longsword_8001.name: Fulgor
Longsword_8001.description: Long ago, a King was gifted this artifact by someone who valued his sense of dream, justice, love and kindness, hoping to help him carve these principles into the world.
Longsword_8001.effect: Gain 10% action speed. When you hit an enemy, cause a thunderbolt dealing 20 magical damage.

Zweihander_8001.name: Bloodthirst
Zweihander_8001.description: This massive sword was tempered in uncountable rivers of blood. Still insatiable, it drives its wielder to crave more until their final breath.
Zweihander_8001.effect: Hitting a target heals you for 0.02% of the damage dealt, and inflicts a Bleed that deals 30 physical damage for 5 seconds.

RecurveBow_8001.name: Pestilence
RecurveBow_8001.description: Capable of spreading poison that will have itâ€™s victims begging for death, this cursed bow once belonged to first of the legendary Four Horseman.
RecurveBow_8001.effect: When you deal damage to an enemy, inflict disease dealing 20 true magical damage for 4 seconds.

CrystalBall_8001.name: Zirkziâ€™s Eye
CrystalBall_8001.description: Unable to defeat a hopelessly powerful demi-god, an ancient sorcerer sacrificed his life to seal one of the demi-god's eyes in a crystal ball.
CrystalBall_8001.effect: If the spell hits the target, Death's Gaze deals an additional 2 true magical damage to the enemy.

Spellbook_8001.name: Spellweaver
Spellbook_8001.description: A rare spellbook pulsing with arcane energy, whispering ancient secrets in an unknown language. Rumored to have been taken from a mysterious land only accessible through special portals.
Spellbook_8001.effect: Successfully casting a spell increases your casting speed by 5%, up to 5 times. The effect lasts for 5 seconds and is reset each time it increases.

Halberd_8001.name: Cinder
Halberd_8001.description: It will be difficult to keep track of your kill count for they have all been reduced to a pile of ash.
Halberd_8001.effect:
When you hit an enemy, deal an additional 10 magical damage and burn the target over 9 seconds.

Burn: The target takes 27 fire magical damage.

WarMaul_8001.name: Leviathan
WarMaul_8001.description: A War Maul reinforced with the hardened hide of a ferocious beast. With a single swing, it can alter the course of currents and summon a torrent of crashing waters.
WarMaul_8001.effect:
When swung, the weapon emits waves that follow its trajectory. These waves inflict the wet status on targets for 2 seconds, deal 10 _ to enemies, and restore 10 health to allies over 3 seconds.

Wet: The target loses -20% move speed bonus and jump height is reduced by 0%.

Rapier_8001.name: Viola
Rapier_8001.description: The chill of winter flows in the wake of this icy blade. Gifted from the Winter Fae who wanted to prove there is nothing stronger than the cold bite of their domain.
Rapier_8001.effect:
Attacking enemies with this weapon deals an additional 10 magical damage, inflicting frostbite for 2 seconds.

Frostbite: The target loses -20% move speed bonus and -20% action speed.

StilettoDagger_8001.name: Deathbloom
StilettoDagger_8001.description: Thou love me, thou love me not... Thou love me, thou love me not...
StilettoDagger_8001.effect: When you deal damage to a target, cause a death flower to bloom. After 3 have bloomed, the death blossoms explode, dealing 30 true magical damage.

Spear_8001.name: Abyssal Trident
Spear_8001.description: Embodying the unfulfilled desires of the Fallen King of the Sea, the sharp tip of this spear constantly drips with the frigid waters of the deep abyss.
Spear_8001.effect:
Deals an additional 10 ice magical damage and inflicts wet for 3 seconds on hit.

Wet: The target loses -20% move speed bonus and jump height is reduced by 0%.

Longbow_8001.name: Nipalan
Longbow_8001.description: A bow crafted by a legendary tribe of warriors known as the Penobscots. So terrifyingly strong it knocks back their foes.
Longbow_8001.effect: Gain  weapon damage and push the hit target back.

MorningStar_8001.name: Pulverizing Prayer
MorningStar_8001.description: Gifted to a holy fighter long ago by a demi-god, proving faith is also a powerful weapon, crushing all non-believers.
MorningStar_8001.effect: When you deal damage to an enemy, crush their armor, reducing their physical damage reduction by -25% for 10 seconds. This effect stacks up to 3 times.

ArmingSword_8001.name: Kumaâ€™s Claw
ArmingSword_8001.description: Forged from the flames of a mighty black dragon, this sword claws at the target's soul, inflicting lethal damage.

Falchion_8001.name: Kumaâ€™s Fang
Falchion_8001.description: Seems the great black dragon has lost a tooth... No matter, it will continue its bloody purpose.

CrystalSword_8001.name: Catice
CrystalSword_8001.description: A sword forged from the shards of the Ice Queen's tears. Though fragile and prone to breaking, its fierce icy blade summons delicate whirlwinds of snowflakes, reforming itself to its original form.
CrystalSword_8001.effect: Upon hitting a target or object, the blade violently shatters. If the blade hits a target, shatter will deal up to an additional 25 ice magical damage. The broken blade regenerates to its original state over 4 seconds, reducing shatter damage until the blade is fully reformed.

WizardStaff_8001.name: Illusory
WizardStaff_8001.description: Rumored to be crafted by a powerful yet mischievous trickster from another realm, who delighted in confusing and outsmarting their enemies.
WizardStaff_8001.effect: A successful spell cast makes the user invisible for 4 seconds and leaves the user's illusion temporarily.

SurvivalBow_8001.name: Elven Bow of Truth
SurvivalBow_8001.description: A bow made by the elves by forging the branches of the tree of truth.
SurvivalBow_8001.effect: Gain 25% action speed and fire arrows that fly in a straight line.

Buckler_8001.name: Delirium
Buckler_8001.description: Created by a mad alchemist, using dragon's blood in some of his creations. Beware, its side effects can be just as potent as they are perilous.
Buckler_8001.effect: When held in hand, maximum health is reduced by -5%, but regenerates 2 health per second.

BattleAxe_8001.name: Echo of Screams
BattleAxe_8001.description: An ancient axe imbued with the screams of fallen enemies, granting its wielder a deadly strength that comes from the echoes of the past.
BattleAxe_8001.effect: Deal 20 true magical damage to the target and cause the target to only hear their own screams for 3 seconds.

FellingAxe_8001.name: Soulscraper
FellingAxe_8001.description: Through a bond that transcended realms, a guardian of souls granted a mortal companion this enchanted axe.
FellingAxe_8001.effect: Each time you deal damage, absorb the targets soul and gain 5 strength, 5 vigor for 12 seconds. This effect stacks up to 3 times.

Quarterstaff_8001.name: Stinky Stick
Quarterstaff_8001.effect: When you deal damage to a target, gain 0.1% chance to emit a poison cloud for 12 seconds, dealing 15 magical damage every second to enemies within its area. Up to 3 poison clouds can exist at a time and the wielder is immune to damage from poison clouds.

DoubleAxe_8001.name: Life after Death
DoubleAxe_8001.description:
Death comes for us all one day...
Is today that day?
DoubleAxe_8001.effect: When receiving a killing blow, the wielder becomes invincible and remains at 1 Health for 3 seconds. This effect can only be triggered once during an adventure. Does not trigger while on cooldown.

HeaterShield_8001.name: Aegis
HeaterShield_8001.description: Crafted by a powerful and mysterious being to aid in eliminating magic users. He saw wizards lust for magic, fearing they would grow too powerful.
HeaterShield_8001.effect: While in defensive stance, gain the ability to deflect incoming spells. When a spell is reflected, the effect continues for 8 seconds. You may not reflect spells again for 12 seconds.

HorsemansAxe_8001.name: Famine
HorsemansAxe_8001.description: This enchanted axe is crafted by infusing the blood and essence from the third of the legendary Four Horsemen.
HorsemansAxe_8001.effect: When you deal damage to a target, render them unable to receive incoming healing for 20 seconds.
